comment:
She was at court representing the sun (NGN) as their witness,.. not for herself, and only because she was their source for the story after she sold them, ‚ÄòHer Truth‚Äô not, ‚ÄòThe Truth.‚Äô 


Therefore, as she was only there as a witness, all she had to do was give her testimony across the 4 days. But, no, she chose to stay, to attend throughout the trial as it gave her more options to torment him,... garnering publicity while playing the role of victim. She even went as far as to try to blame his side for forcing her to be there. That bit was ridiculous, when they tried to stop her attending as it was the sun and Dan Wootton they were suing for libel, not her,‚Ä¶ and Depp and Heard is a whole other trial. Then again, people and the media should know that as it was covered,‚Ä¶ a win for her and NGN when the court went against the ruling to keep her away. 

Plus, think about it, if she's a victim of domestic abuse, why weren't they her very first words when she spoke to the press on those steps so dramatically before the case was even over? 
All she spoke of in her scripted speech was being traumatised as her life with Johnny was now out in the world. It was nothing more than a PR stunt for damage control when she realised people were beginning to see exactly what kind of person she is... a habitual liar who targeted and victimised a man for her own gain. 

Why is there such biased reporting on this case? 
The only thing they used as evidence over him not possibly being a victim here was due to his drinking and drug taking - which he‚Äôs never hidden... 

Now, if that kind of evidence was used for the reasoning as to why a woman, a female wasn‚Äôt abused, the public would be up in arms. Cries of, her lifestyle having nothing to do with anything would be heard, but in this case, it's seen as a reasonable and justifiable as he's a male. 

Where's the equality now?

Where's the discussions about true abuse victims,... stories which prove abusers are not just males? 

Where's the talks about the studies and collated data which proves abuse has no gender and is, in fact, committed by both males and females, in both heterosexual and LGBTQ+ relationships. 

When is the media going to be fair and unbiased in their reporting and not just push the narrative of believe all women? 
When is there going to be discussions about evidence and that there is, in fact, two sides to a story?

In fact, talking about evidence, where's her medical reports? Where is the photographic evidence showing swelling and stitches? Surely there should be hospital reports over visits she made to have stitches done or to have limbs put in casts while her broken bones healed due to all these beatings she received from him?

These are the questions you should be asking because, let's face it, if he did just half of what she's accused him of, she'd have been in intensive care or worse...
